{"word":"κολοβός","slug":"κολοβός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κολοβός</b></el> <el>(κολοβός, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κόλος'><el>κόλος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>docked, curtailed</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>κολοβὸς κεράτων</el>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>truncus pedum</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <el>κ. χειρῶν</el> <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>maimed, mutilated</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}